current_position:
Led conception and completion of four short documentaries; screening at DOC NYC, Muay Film Festival, and more.
Currently producing " Fighting Back," a documentary featuring a female Muay Thai fighter empowering AAPI women through self-defense classes to combat anti-Asian hate. The film addresses intergenerational trauma and explores critical social justice issues.

description:
Make a positive impact from visual storytelling, including documentary film production & project management.

I am a project manager, independent documentary filmmaker based in New York focused on women's rights and social justice. I am a visual storyteller who is good at revealing character's emotional world with a sociology and journalism background. I am also a member of Asian American Documentary Network and the Video Consortium.
